      "side": 1,
      "message": "My guess for the crash: glVertexAttribPointer below picks up the data or offset to use in the VBO based on the current GL_ARRAY_BUFFER binding. Now that we set the GL_ARRAY_BUFFER binding to 0 here, the glVertexAttribPointer below causes corrupt memory or segfaults immediately, because it thinks it got a CPU-side pointer, or it is looking for an offset into a buffer that we shadow on the host that is not there, or the underlying host GPU driver is looking at the wrong buffer.\n\nAnother caveat that is semi-related: The Translator has been subtly core-profiled here; it assumes the guest always provides it with either offsets into GL buffers, or calls a special guest-\u003ehost serialization glVertexAttribPointerWithDataSize that holds the number of bytes of CPU-side pointers to use. Please try not to use glVertexAttribPointer with CPU-side pointers in this setting :)",
